{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Cultural practices, including framing, have also been shown to diffuse both within and across movements (Soule and Roggeband, 2018).",
    "Movements also exist in direct competition with opposing countermovements.",
    "As one of the primary goals of collective action framing is to \"demobilize antagonists\" (Snow et al., 1988), frames develop over the course of sustained interaction with countermovements (Ayoub and Chetaille, 2020).",
    "Movement and countermovement frames may be closely-aligned, especially when drawing from the same cultural themes (Ayoub and Chetaille, 2020; Sun et al., 2023).",
    "At the same time, movements may develop frames to challenge or contest the opposition's (McCaffrey and Keys*, 2000; Stewart et al., 2017)."
  ],
